Title: Effects of inhibitory control training on behavioural control during acute alcohol consumption
Description: The aim of this experiment is to investigate whether a computer-based training task that is designed to improve behavioural control, can offset the detriments in behavioural control that are associated with acute alcohol intoxication.
Contributors: Olivia Maynard
Tags: TARG, Tobacco and Alcohol Research Group, University of Bristol, School of Experimental Psychology

Effects of inhibitory control training on behavioural control during acute alcohol consumption
The aim of this experiment is to investigate whether a computer-based training task that is designed to improve behavioural control, can offset the detriments in behavioural control that are associated with acute alcohol intoxication.
